    <sectiondef kind="user-defined">
      <header>Command Macros</header>
      <description><para>IEEE 802.15.4 net management commands.</para>
<para>These IEEE 802.15.4 subsystem net management commands can be called by applications via <ref refid="group__net__mgmt" kindref="compound">Network Management</ref> macro.</para>
<para>All attributes and parameters are given in CPU byte order (scalars) or big endian (byte arrays) unless otherwise specified.</para>
<para>The following IEEE 802.15.4 MAC management service primitives are referenced in this enumeration:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>MLME-ASSOCIATE.request, see section 8.2.3</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>MLME-DISASSOCIATE.request, see section 8.2.4</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>MLME-SET/GET.request, see section 8.2.6</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>MLME-SCAN.request, see section 8.2.11</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>The following IEEE 802.15.4 MAC data service primitives are referenced in this enumeration:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>MLME-DATA.request, see section 8.3.2</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>MAC PIB attributes (mac.../sec...): see sections 8.4.3 and 9.5. PHY PIB attributes (phy...): see section 11.3. Both are accessed through MLME-SET/GET primitives. </para>
</description>
